RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAJOR DEAL was off mid pack in the three path, slowly advanced up the back side into a stalking position behind the leaders, edged out into the four path nearing the five sixteenth pole, launched a bid and took the lead at the quarter pole, was kept on point and lightly encouraged down the strretch and got the win. MORO LEGEND was well off of the pace and racing in the two path, was allowed to settle in hands, launched a bid after the half mile pole, saved ground through the turn, passed rivals at the quarter pole, chased the eventual winner down through the stretch, repelling an outside challenger, could not get to the the winner but was second best today. POINT BLANK was off the pace early, raced in the three path near the b ack of the field early on, inched out into the four path and launched a bid passing the first set of rivals at the half mile pole, edged out into the four path and passed rivals through the turn, battled in the upper stretch wit and inside foe and down the lane for second place but did not have enough today finishing third. COUNTRY CUT was strong in the bridle and went from mid pack into stalking the early pace setter right away, stalked that foe until the five sixteenth pole, was passed on the outside by another contender and faded. SUPER INTENSE willingly led, was three and four wide early, shifted into the two path, led until the three eighths pole and faded through the turn. LIT A SHUCK stalked for a quarter mile and then faded.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 2w, saved ground, clean trip, closed, second best
